<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: The Monopoly of Banded Mail will stop! This concerns ALL citizens of Norrath (lng txt)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Tybolt">Tybolt</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:47 a.m. 20/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: The Monopoly of Banded Mail will stop! This concerns ALL citizens of Norrath (lng txt)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/veeshan.cgi?read=107" TARGET=_self>The Monopoly of Banded Mail will stop! This concerns ALL citizens of Norrath (lng txt)</A> (Kiron of Sacred Haven)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Shiron is only following the very simple laws of business and nothing more. Your plight is understood, but idealistic and naive. I mean this in the greatest amount of respect possible and do not take offense. I wish I could buy banded goods, but alas I do not have the money. However, Shiron has EVERY right to charge what he wants, and if he has taken the time to establish a network of smiths in order to make money and do business then more power to him. And he has also found his niche in Norrath. If you want to compete, then more power to you, but what Shiron did in response was only good business and if you see it as a monopoly then you are misconstruing the definition from the dictionary. So go find your own niche and let the man conduct business as he sees fit, he has taken the time, learned the skill and applied to to making a living. Leave him alone.

<P>Tybolt
<P>PS - I am not a blacksmith by the way, just so you know this was an unbias response.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
